The paper discusses the use of automated static analysis for quality assurance in software development, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The specific techniques used, such as code clone detection and bug pattern detection, are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). The paper also addresses the issue of risk management and avoiding bugs, which could fall under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the results of the analysis and the usefulness of the techniques, which could involve machine learning (cs.LG) in terms of evaluating the effectiveness of the analysis.
